---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../data/tools";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Free Online Tools Nest"
  description="Read the privacy policy of Free Online Tools Nest. Discover how our client-side browser tools ensure 100% data privacy and security."
  canonicalPath="/privacy-policy/"
>
  <div class="container-narrow py-12 md:py-20">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing: -1.28px;">
      Privacy Policy
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-mute mb-10">Last updated: June 2026</p>

    <article class="space-y-6 text-body leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing: -0.6px;">Overview</h2>
        <p>
          {SITE.name} ("{SITE.domain}") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your information when you use our website and tools.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 font-medium text-ink">
          The short version: we do not collect, store, or transmit your data. All tool processing happens locally in your web browser.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing: -0.6px;">Data Processing</h2>
        <p>
          All tools on this website process data entirely within your browser using client-side JavaScript. No data you enter into any tool is sent to our servers, stored in any database, or shared with any third party. When you close the page, your data is gone.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing: -0.6px;">Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We may collect the following non-personal information:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 mt-2">
          <li>Anonymous usage analytics (page views, tool usage counts) — if analytics is enabled</li>
          <li>Device type, browser type, and general location (country level) from analytics</li>
          <li>Information you voluntarily submit through our contact form</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">We do not collect personal data, passwords, or any content you enter into our tools.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing: -0.6px;">Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          We use a single localStorage key to remember your dark mode preference. We do not use tracking cookies. If analytics is enabled, it may use minimal cookies for session tracking — these are never used for advertising.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing: -0.6px;">Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          We load fonts from Google Fonts, which has its own privacy policy. We may use privacy-focused analytics (like Plausible or similar) that do not use cookies and comply with GDPR without consent. We do not use any advertising networks.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing: -0.6px;">Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
          Under GDPR and similar regulations, you have the right to access, correct, or delete any personal data we hold about you. Since we do not store personal data from tool usage, this primarily applies to contact form submissions. Contact us at the address below to exercise these rights.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing: -0.6px;">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about this privacy policy, please <a href="/contact/" class="text-link hover:text-link-deep underline">contact us</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
